snippet.title: Dog-smuggling charges dropped against Amber Heard
snippet.description:
American actress Amber Heard has pleaded guilty to providing false immigration documents, when she entered Australia last year with her pet dogs. Heard appeared in an apology video with her actor husband, Johnny Depp, which was played at an Australian courthouse on Monday, as part of her court appearance. Prosecutors have dropped charges against Heard of illegally "smuggling" her pet dogs into the country without proper permits.
